    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><strong>Last updated: April 2026</strong></p>

    <h2>What We Collect</h2>
    <p>CalcPhi is a static website. All calculator inputs are processed locally in your browser — no calculator data is transmitted to our servers or stored anywhere.</p>
    <p>We use Google Analytics 4 (GA4) to collect anonymised usage data: pages visited, approximate geographic region, browser type, and device type. This data is aggregated and does not identify individual users. You can opt out using the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="nofollow noopener">Google Analytics opt-out extension</a>.</p>
    <p>We display Google AdSense advertisements. Google may use cookies to serve personalised ads based on your browsing history. See <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="nofollow noopener">Google's Privacy Policy</a> for details.</p>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>CalcPhi itself does not set any first-party cookies. Third-party cookies may be set by Google Analytics and Google AdSense. You can control cookies in your browser settings or use a browser extension to block third-party cookies.</p>

    <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
    <p>CalcPhi pages may link to third-party websites (banks, fund houses, financial products). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those sites.</p>

    <h2>Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
    <p>Some links on CalcPhi are affiliate links. If you open an account or apply for a product through a CalcPhi affiliate link, we may receive a commission. This does not affect our editorial recommendations — we only link to products we consider genuinely relevant to the calculator context.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>For privacy-related enquiries: <a href="mailto:privacy@calcphi.com">privacy@calcphi.com</a></p>
  </div>
